projects: [{'title': 'In-House days / Workshops', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2011}, 'end': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2011}}, 'description': '- NLR\n- Dutch Space', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Jonatan', 'last_name': 'Leloux', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Space Engineer & Software Engineer'}]}, {'title': 'Hot air balloon - Android measurement app', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}, 'description': 'Development of an Android app for KNMI, which measures the position, velocity, bearing, acceleration, magnetic field, pressure and their accuracy during a hot air balloon flight. Their measured data is logged on a server, and is a good source of input for weather models, as weather measurements at the altitude of a hot air balloon are scarce.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Jonatan', 'last_name': 'Leloux', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Space Engineer & Software Engineer'}]}, {'title': 'MSc Thesis: Filtering Techniques for Orbital Debris Conjunction Analysis', 'date': {'start': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2010}, 'end': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2012}}, 'description': 'Verified implementation of a complete orbital debris conjunction analysis system, including the improved design of multiple versions of filters and sieves, which were tested in terms of performance, for a more efficient and reliable process.
